    <text id="F0643T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Hover mentions his fear of the draft and asks about his family and friends.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mother</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-11-02">November the 2nd A. D. 1864 </date>
                        <name type="place">HeadQuarters Near the <orig reg="Shenandoah">Shenode</orig>
                            valley </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mother </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I take the opportunity of writing a few lines to let you know that i am well. At
                    present hoping this few lines will find you in the same state of good health
                    Mother I may let you know of the late enlistment of my <orig reg="self"
                    >selfe</orig> to the U. S. service I enlisted on the 14 of september the reason
                    I enlisted was I was afraid of the draft. I wish I know if any of our boys have
                    been drafted i would like to know if Franklin Walker has been drafted or not. I
                    would like to know how little Idea is getting along. No more at present but</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute><orig reg="remain">remains</orig> your affectionate son </salute>
                    <signed>Augustus Hover </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Please write soon </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
